task.summary: Default task
Added a new experimental .ui file.
When executing Graphs, a Runner is spawned which creates a Graph instance based to data send to it via socket.
The remote runner will now execute graphs when not paused.
Changed a lot of StyleSheets.
Changed save state data structure from dictionary to list to make sure node IDs stay the same after pushing a graph to a remote interpreter.
Added a DROP command to remote interpreters (untested) TODO: Implement a loop body notification system. Fix concurrent loop node problem. Add features to STATUS command. Add dynamic UPDATE command.

Dynamic Graph updates seem to be working. Former UPDATE command was renamed to PUSH. UPDATE is now only adding new Nodes to the graph without reistantiating already existing ones. Also, all connections are deleted and then recreated. So far, UPDATES are purely constructive meaning Nodes removed in the editor are not deleted at the remote interpreter side. This is only an issue if it is a root Node that requires no inputs. TODO: Implement a loop body notification system. Fix concurrent loop node problem. Add features to STATUS command. Add removal of deleted Nodes on the remote interpreter side.

The UPDATE command now also updates Nodes's deault values. TODO: Implement a loop body notification system. Fix concurrent loop node problem. Add features to STATUS command. Add removal of deleted Nodes on the remote interpreter side.
Deleted Nodes are now deleted on the interpreter side. TODO: Implement a loop body notification system. Fix concurrent loop node problem. Add features to STATUS command.
Restyled the settings dialog.
Fixed an issue with ForEach nodes. Showing plots now works on Windows machines, too. Hopefully it still works on Linux systems.
Did some testing on how to dynamically create Node classes at run time.
Ported to QtWebEngine and added quickPlot.py to draw simple plots without library overhead.
Started implementing a more flexible template system.
Added color coding to templates.
Small changes for testing purposes.
Fixed missing color value error in templates.py module.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/JLuebben/floppy
# Conflicts: # floppy/node.py # floppy/painter.py # floppy/reportWidget.py # floppy/templates.py
Reimplemented the ProgramTemplate with the new template system. WIP.
Hopefully successfully merged the branches.
Added remote interpreter 'executable' and a short description how to use the interpreter remotely.
Box selection is now working while being zoomed in or out. Fixes #1.
The Node.report method will now also return information about whether a node is ready to be executed. This information is then displayed in the ReportWidget. This is not working for ControlNodes yet.
The ready report now works for Loops as well.
More stuff for getting macros to work.
Creating Subgraphs will now create a custom node class with the appropriate inputs and outputs.
Selector offset issue seems to be resolved. Missed a hard-coded margin value. Fixes #3
WaitAny Node should now work correctly. Fixes #4
Fixed issue with re-executing loop nodes and the optional TRIGGER input.
Switch Nodes will now work within Loops. Fixes #9
Fixed error in SwitchNode's notify method that prevented correct behavior when the node was placed within a loop. Fixes #9
Control inputs now support multiple connections. The corresponding availability check will only return True if the input was set as many times as the input has connections.
